						               													<description>Kangaroo Disco Mania is a fun, family friendly game centered around matching icons on custom cards to get the most points for the craziest moves. Each card has charming, custom artwork centered around animals doing the Disco. The game typically plays in 10-15 minutes and has multiple game modes to scale the gameplay in the interest of maintaining that quick-paced play. All modes except the solo mode have a built-in timer made up of cards, called the &amp;quot;song&amp;quot;, that can be claimed for additional points but also shortening the game time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The core of the game is centered around matching arrays of icons along the tops and bottoms of the cards to get the most points. It is a simple enough concept to allow younger family members to play, however the ability to continue playing if you set up &amp;quot;perfect matches&amp;quot; allows strategies to pull off crazy and long combinations that will keep more experienced players having fun alongside them. In addition to its quick gameplay, the game lacks a true &amp;quot;fail&amp;quot; condition and players who go out on their turn are turned into audience members with a new set of actions that can still influence the rest of the &amp;quot;dancers&amp;quot; still playing for points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
